Note on the 🔥 "Author-original (JP, 改変禁止)" lines in critical-rules.md:

These lines reproduce the original Japanese wording of the rules verbatim,
per R16 (the do-not-modify principle). The MIT License above grants you the
legal right to modify any part of this software, including those lines. We
*recommend* (not legally bind) keeping those lines verbatim when redistributing,
because rewording them tends to silently drift the rule's intent. If you fork
and reword them, please call out the change in your README so downstream users
know they are reading a derivative, not the canonical wording.
